<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36024b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36024b">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36024b"> 24(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Avenida de Mayo / Belgrano / Flores / conventillos</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Avenida Alvear is particularly noted for the elegance of its private residences, and the new <mark>Avenida de Mayo</mark> for its display of elaborately ornamented public and business edifices, while the suburban districts of <mark>Belgrano and Flores</mark> are distinguished for the attractiveness of their county-houses and gardens. A part of the population is greatly over-crowded, one-fifth living in <i><mark>conventillos</mark></i>, or tenement-houses. <small> &ldquo;BUENOS AIRES&rdquo; <a name="EBBA" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBBA"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 753a</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
